{meta: title Kiss on the Door}
{meta: artist Hank Locklin}
{meta: composer Lawton Williams}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I sat there alone on your door [G7]step
[C]The note said you'd gone to the store
[F]I waited for you till two this morning
[G7]Then I left you a kiss on the [C]door
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]I left you a kiss on the [C]door
[G7]For I won't kiss your lips any more
[C]I know now that you have walked out on [F]me
[G7]So I left you a kiss on the [C]door
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
